This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques for sentiment analysis. Specifically, it focuses on the E2E-ABSA task, which involves identifying aspects and their corresponding sentiment in a given text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also uses neural networks and deep learning techniques, which are covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for identifying aspects, which falls under the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses BERT, a popular pre-trained language model, which is a neural network architecture and falls under the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
